description: String resources, ellipsis, and multi-language values
globs:
  - app/src/main/res/values/**/*.xml
  - app/src/main/res/values-*/**/*.xml
alwaysApply: false
---

# String resources

- Do not hardcode user-visible strings in Kotlin or XML when a string resource exists or should exist.
- Use the ellipsis character `…` (or `&#8230;` in XML), not three ASCII periods.
- When adding or changing a default-language string, add the same logical entry for every locale the app ships (`values`, `values-sr`, and any other `values-*` folders in this project).
